1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,337
In 2008, quantitative models at every major bank said a nationwide

2
00:00:05,437 --> 00:00:11,516
simultaneous decline in US housing prices was essentially impossible — such

3
00:00:11,616 --> 00:00:16,377
an event had never happened in the historical data. Then it

4
00:00:16,477 --> 00:00:21,980
happened. In May 2022, quantitative models at every crypto fund said

5
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:27,335
a top-5 algorithmic stablecoin collapsing to zero in 72 hours was

6
00:00:27,435 --> 00:00:34,008
essentially impossible. Then it happened. Nassim Nicholas Taleb calls these Black

7
00:00:34,108 --> 00:00:38,787
Swan events — and his framework for thinking about them is

8
00:00:38,887 --> 00:00:44,060
the most important risk management insight of the last 50 years.

9
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:49,293
Welcome to QuantiFire. Taleb's trilogy — The Black Swan, Fooled

10
00:00:49,393 --> 00:00:56,383
by Randomness, and Antifragile — fundamentally challenged the mathematical assumptions

11
00:00:56,483 --> 00:01:01,825
underlying modern portfolio theory. This final episode of Season 1

12
