closes the loop: after 35 episodes of models and formulas,

13
00:01:06,706 --> 00:01:11,141
we confront the limits of models themselves and build a

14
00:01:11,241 --> 00:01:16,500
practical framework for surviving the events they cannot predict.

15
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:24,927
The core statistical problem: financial returns live in Extremistan — domains

16
00:01:25,027 --> 00:01:30,937
dominated by extreme outliers. The blue curve is the normal distribution

17
00:01:31,037 --> 00:01:35,779
— what your model assumes. The red curve is the fat-tailed

18
00:01:35,879 --> 00:01:41,538
Student-t distribution with 3 degrees of freedom — closer to reality.

19
00:01:41,638 --> 00:01:48,300
Notice the shaded tails beyond 3 standard deviations: the fat-tailed distribution

20
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:53,224
has 10 to 100 times more probability mass in extreme events

21
00:01:53,324 --> 00:01:59,068
than the normal distribution predicts. The 2008 financial crisis was a

22
00:01:59,168 --> 00:02:05,328
25-sigma event under normal distribution assumptions — an event that should

23
00:02:05,428 --> 00:02:10,003
occur once every 10 to the power 135 years. It occurred.

24
00:02:10,103 --> 00:02:15,094
This is the Ludic Fallacy — using models built for structured

25
00:02:15,194 --> 00:02:20,771
games to model open-ended reality. September 11 didn't appear in any

26
00:02:20,871 --> 00:02:27,532
historical dataset. COVID-19 didn't appear in any historical dataset. The model's

27
00:02:27,632 --> 00:02:30,788
confidence interval is not a guarantee.

28
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:39,194
Taleb defines a Black Swan by three properties. First: rarity —

29
00:02:39,294 --> 00:02:45,054
the event lies outside the realm of regular expectations. Nothing in

30
00:02:45,154 --> 00:02:51,343
the past convincingly points to its possibility. Second: extreme impact —

31
00:02:51,443 --> 00:02:57,892
the event carries massive consequences, positive or negative. It changes the

32
00:02:57,992 --> 00:03:05,216
paradigm. Third: retrospective predictability — after the event, it seems explainable

33
00:03:05,316 --> 00:03:10,902
and predictable in hindsight. 'Of course the housing market was in

34
00:03:11,002 --> 00:03:17,020
a bubble.' 'Of course an algorithmic stablecoin with no real collateral

35
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:22,621
would collapse.' Hindsight bias kicks in. The term comes from the

36
00:03:22,721 --> 00:03:28,393
assumption, held until the 17th century, that all swans were white.

37
00:03:28,493 --> 00:03:34,339
The discovery of black swans in Australia invalidated a universal law

38
00:03:34,439 --> 00:03:38,302
based on extensive but incomplete observation.

39
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:49,750
Taleb's prescription: build antifragile portfolios — portfolios that gain from volatility,

40
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:56,041
not just survive it. The Barbell Strategy: 90% in ultra-safe assets

41
00:03:56,141 --> 00:04:00,923
— T-bills, FDIC cash — you cannot lose more than 10%

42
00:04:01,023 --> 00:04:07,308
of total portfolio. 10% in highly convex, positively skewed assets —

43
00:04:07,408 --> 00:04:15,665
long options, venture bets, tail-risk hedging instruments. These positions have unlimited

44
00:04:15,765 --> 00:04:21,580
upside but limited downside — maximum loss is the premium paid.

45
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:28,622
Net result: protected from catastrophic loss while having exposure to Black

46
00:04:28,722 --> 00:04:34,068
Swan upside. Applied to DeFi: 70 to 80% in stablecoins and

47
00:04:34,168 --> 00:04:39,889
major chain staking, 10 to 20% in diversified DeFi blue chips,

48
00:04:39,989 --> 00:04:45,241
and 5 to 10% in protocol tokens with convex upside. Never

49
00:04:45,341 --> 00:04:51,626
concentrate more than 20% in any single protocol regardless of audit

50
00:04:51,726 --> 00:04:57,260
status or track record. Black Swans don't care about audits.

51
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:04,493
Build portfolios that can survive Black Swans, not just model the

52
00:05:04,593 --> 00:05:10,805
expected distribution of normal outcomes. Rules: never size any position where

53
00:05:10,905 --> 00:05:15,741
a total loss destroys your ability to continue. Keep cash and

54
00:05:15,841 --> 00:05:22,458
safe assets sufficient to survive multi-year drawdowns. Maintain convex exposure to

55
00:05:22,558 --> 00:05:27,799
upside as Black Swan insurance. Models tell you what should happen

56
00:05:27,899 --> 00:05:33,059
— position sizing tells you what happens when they're wrong. That

57
